Hi, as i remember they are already implemented using attached properties in <strong>DragBehaviour</strong> class.<br />
You can edit them in the <strong>VertexControl</strong> template using smth like this:<br />
<pre><code>xmlns:extbehaviour=&quot;clr-namespace:WPFExtensions.AttachedBehaviours;assembly=WPFExtensions&quot;

        &lt;Setter Property=&quot;extbehaviour:DragBehaviour.IsDragEnabled&quot;
                Value=&quot;True&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;Setter Property=&quot;extbehaviour:DragBehaviour.X&quot;
                Value=&quot;{Binding RelativeSource={RelativeSource Self},Path=(Controls:GraphCanvas.X),Mode=TwoWay}&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;Setter Property=&quot;extbehaviour:DragBehaviour.Y&quot;
                Value=&quot;{Binding RelativeSource={RelativeSource Self},Path=(Controls:GraphCanvas.Y),Mode=TwoWay}&quot; /&gt;</code></pre>

Also you can take a look at <a href="http://graphx.codeplex.com" rel="nofollow">http://graphx.codeplex.com</a><br />
This is my enchancement of Graph# project.<br />
